Package: audyn
Version: 1.0.0
Section: sound
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Depends: python3 (>= 3.10), python3-pip, python3-venv, nginx, pipewire, libopus0, libogg0
Recommends: pipewire-audio-client-libraries, wireplumber
Maintainer: B. Wynne <admin@audyn.local>
Description: Professional Audio Capture & Archival Engine
 Audyn is a professional-grade audio capture and archival system
 designed for broadcast and production environments.
 .
 Features:
  - AES67/SMPTE ST 2110-30 audio capture
  - PipeWire local audio capture
  - WAV and Opus output formats
  - Time-based file rotation with multiple naming layouts
  - Real-time audio level metering
  - Web-based management interface
  - Microsoft Entra ID authentication with RBAC
 .
 The web interface is accessible on the management network while
 AES67 capture operates on a dedicated audio network interface.
Homepage: https://github.com/brianwynne/Audyn
